data.description: Step into 748 7th Street Southeast, Unit C, and experience a residence that redefines what you can make your own! Boasting an expansive 1965 square feet, this modernized home offers more space than a typical row home and features 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, separate spacious living and dining room and a family room off the kitchen, providing ample room for relaxation and privacy. The inviting family room, a rare find in the area, opens up to an inviting roof deck, offering a seamless indoor-outdoor living experience.  Not just your regular row home with tight and dark spaces, and certainly more than a typical condo, this residence presents the best of both worlds. The thoughtfully designed layout with an abundance of natural light and contemporary updates elevates this home, making it a standout in this close in Capitol Hill location! With its unmatched space, gracious primary bedroom with a room-sized walk in closet and newly renovated primary bath, off street parking, and a family room leading to a roof deck, 748 7th Street Southeast, Unit C, is a rare option that offers a lifestyle of elegance and comfort. And it's not just beautiful and functional, but practical too - with a long list of multiple recent updates such as a newer AC, furnace, water heater, W/D, 36" gas range, Bosch dishwasher, this lovely home is the perfect package! Walk to: Eastern Market, Barracks Row, 40+ restaurants, Metro, Navy Yard, Yards Park, 2 award winning gyms, Whole Foods...need we say more? Have your agent show it to you or visit us at our open house this weekend!
